  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A proposed IFC investment of $20 million in Carlyle Mexico Partners, L.P. (Carlyle Mexico) a private equity fund with target commitments of $250 million.  The Fund is sponsored by The Carlyle Group (Carlyle) to invest in buyout or other private equity opportunities in Mexico and in U.S. companies that have a significant Hispanic customer base or cross-border initiatives.  The Fund will target medium and large companies.  The Fund expects to make 5-8 investments of between $20-50 million, acquiring controlling or significant minority stakes.</narrative>
  </description>
